Authorities say claims in a voice note that has been making the rounds that there have been arrests in connection with the fire are unfounded. CAPE TOWN – Police have rubbished claims of an arrest for arson in connection with the Knysna fires. The blaze swept through the Garden Route area this week fanned on by gale force winds brought on by an intense cold front. At least five people have died as a direct cause of the flames and 390 properties were destroyed. Southern Cape Police's Malcolm Poje said: “No arrest has been made concerning the Knysna fires. The rumours that have been making the rounds in a voice note that an arsonist has been arrested is completely unfounded. The origin or cause of the fire has not been established, as this is an ongoing investigation by the departments involved.